## Document Fabrication Prevention (for factual/legal docs)

**When generating any document containing facts about real people, cases, or organizations, apply these checks.**

### The Five Fabrication Patterns

| Pattern | Detection |
|---------|-----------|
| Fabricated case citations | Grep for citation patterns, verify each against source |
| Fabricated phone numbers | Grep all phone numbers, verify each in source |
| Completely fabricated people | Every person named must appear in source or be user-stated |
| Party name transposition | Grep every party name occurrence, verify full name |
| Exhibit cross-reference drift | Extract all "Exhibit X" refs, compare against exhibit list |

### Hard Rules
- **Never add a phone number** unless it appears in a source document
- **Never add a case citation** unless it appears in a source document
- **Never name a person** who doesn't appear in source documents
- **Every "Exhibit X" reference** must match the exhibit list in the same document
- When in doubt: omit the fact, don't invent it

